President Barack Obama issued a proclamation honoring the victims of the attack on police officers in Baton Rouge, Louisiana. The proclamation orders that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff at the White House, public buildings and grounds, military posts and naval stations, and on naval vessels of the Federal Government in the District of Columbia, throughout the United States and its Territories and possessions until sunset on July 22, 2016. It also directs that the flag be flown at half-staff for the same length of time at all United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad, including military facilities and naval vessels and stations.